 or summer primarily in Indiana and the Midwest.</p><p>  Whether you need 
 to find your summer job OR you just want to check out all the cool opport
 unities available to students so you can plan ahead for fall\, come on ov
 er to Alumni Hall in the Indiana Memorial Union.</p><p>  Local employers\
 , non-profits\, and camp programs\, IU departments and on-campus employer
 s\, as well as in-state employer partners will be here to tell you about 
 how you can spend your summer gaining the valuable skills you'll need in 
 whatever career you plan to pursue - all while making money and having so
 me fun\, too! You might even be able to plan and secure your fall on-camp
 us job NOW - come and see!<br /><br />  Advanced registration is not requ
 ired to participate in this event\, however\, we do encourage you to regi
 ster in advance for the fair so we can let employers know you'll be there
 .<br /><br /><strong>Career Exploration &amp\; Student Employment (CESE) 
 is committed to providing access\, equal opportunity and reasonable accom
 modation for individuals with disabilities in employment\, its services\,
  programs\, and activities. To request reasonable accommodation\, contact
 :</strong> Angela Martin at aoshepar@iu.edu</p>
