LOCATION:Online
SUMMARY:Space Cybersecurity Digital Badge
DESCRIPTION:Date: March 27 to June 5\, 2026 (not meeting on Good Friday)T
 uition: $3\,995*Duration: 10 week courseDelivery: Online sessions Fridays
  from 4 to 5 p.m. ET  Cyberattacks\, ranging from hacktivists to organize
 d crime networks and even nation states\, are targeting vulnerable networ
 ks and are frequently successful in stealing funds as well as valuable in
 tellectual property.  At the same time\, there is a booming demand across
  both the public and private sectors for practitioners with this training
 \, with more than 700\,000 openings nationwide for cybersecurity professi
 onals. There is a particular need for those with an expertise in space cy
 bersecurity given the reliance on space-based infrastructure for everythi
 ng from weather forecasting and satellite telecommunications to broadband
  internet.Since Russia's cyberattacks on space-based services (https://ww
 w.cigionline.org/publications/the-first-space-cyber-war-and-the-need-for-
 new-regimes-and-policies/?_gl=1*19p6xc0*_ga*MTY4ODYwMTMzNC4xNzQzNDI2Mjk5*
 _ga_61CH0D2DQW*MTc0MzY5MTM3Ni4yMi4xLjE3NDM2OTIxNDQuNjAuMC4w*_gcl_aw*R0NML
 jE3NDMwMTI0MzMuQ2owS0NRandxSW1fQmhEbkFSSXNBS0JZY211dXhkT0M4ZWwza0tFMzUzSE
 pOTm5sOEJ6TThuUFRTRjRISEtYV0ZIRmExZThuTVBoQVN5d2FBbm5IRUFMd193Y0I.*_gcl_a
 u*NjEyMjMwMTQ2LjE3NDM2OTEzNzc.) provided by commercial US space companies
  during its war on Ukraine\, the cybersecurity of space systems has becom
 e high on the agenda\, spurring discussions at the White House and in Con
 gress\, and a $700 million budget request by the Space Force (https://www
 .darkreading.com/cloud-security/us-space-force-wants-700m-cybersecurity) 
 for this purpose alone. At the same time\, a fast-growing market has emer
 ged (https://www.inc.com/heather-wilde/harness-power-of-space-cybersecuri
 ty-for-growth-opportunity.html)\, with demand for professionals and firms
 .  Participants in the Space Cybersecurity Digital Badge program will gai
 n in-depth understanding of the various cyber threats to space systems as
  well as techniques\, tools\, and best practices to address those threats
 . At the end of the program\, participants will have the capability to de
 velop and implement effective strategies for managing cyber risks to spac
 e systems.  After successful completion of an assurance of learning (asse
 ssment) at the conclusion of the program\, participants will earn the Kel
 ley School of Business Space Cybersecurity Digital Badge. Participants ma
 y also earn 3 credit hours toward the 12 credit hour Kelley School of Bus
 iness Cybersecurity Management Graduate Certificate. The Cybersecurity Ma
 nagement Graduate Certificate (https://kelley.iu.edu/programs/executive-e
 ducation-degrees-certificates/online-certificates/cybersecurity-managemen
 t/index.html) may\, in turn\, be applied to the IU MS in Cybersecurity Ri
 sk Management (https://cyberrisk.iu.edu/?_gl=1*1833cq*_gcl_au*MTU3NDIzMTY
 yNy4xNzQ3MjMzNjYx*_ga*MTc4NDY5NDU2My4xNzMzNjM2NDc4*_ga_61CH0D2DQW*czE3NDc
 yMzA4OTkkbzIwJGcxJHQxNzQ3MjM2Mjc2JGo2MCRsMCRoMCRkMFdsRmYxSkwzaUs1bnoyYmNv
 dmVyY09qMlFscDFNV1R1QQ..).  CISA designation: Your participation in this 
 program and completion of all course requirements earns you 12.0 CPE cred
 its that can go towards the annual credits you need to maintain your CISA
  designation.  * Space ISAC members receive exclusive discounts of up to 
 50% based on membership tier. To learn about and obtain the discount\, pl
 ease reach out to Jade Maloney at jade@spaceisac.org (mailto:jade@spaceis
 ac.org).  * GI/VA: We proudly welcome active-duty service members and vet
 erans to the space cybersecurity program. Recognizing that GI Bill and VA
  education benefits do not apply to this program\, IU is pleased to offer
  a Service Members &amp\; Veterans Scholarship amounting to 30% of the tu
 ition. To receive the scholarship\, please enter the code GI/VA30 during 
 registration. Proof of military or veteran status should be provided by t
 he start date of the program.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Date:</strong> March 27 to June 5
 \, 2026 (not meeting on Good Friday)<br /><strong>Tuition:</strong> $3\,9
 95*<br /><strong>Duration:</strong> 10 week course<br /><strong>Delivery:
 </strong> Online sessions Fridays from 4 to 5 p.m. ET</p><p>  Cyberattack
 s\, ranging from hacktivists to organized crime networks and even nation 
 states\, are targeting vulnerable networks and are frequently successful 
 in stealing funds as well as valuable intellectual property.</p><p>  At t
 he same time\, there is a booming demand across both the public and priva
 te sectors for practitioners with this training\, with more than 700\,000
  openings nationwide for cybersecurity professionals. There is a particul
 ar need for those with an expertise in space cybersecurity given the reli
 ance on space-based infrastructure for everything from weather forecastin
 g and satellite telecommunications to broadband internet.</p><p><a href="
 https://www.cigionline.org/publications/the-first-space-cyber-war-and-the
 -need-for-new-regimes-and-policies/?_gl=1*19p6xc0*_ga*MTY4ODYwMTMzNC4xNzQ
 zNDI2Mjk5*_ga_61CH0D2DQW*MTc0MzY5MTM3Ni4yMi4xLjE3NDM2OTIxNDQuNjAuMC4w*_gc
 l_aw*R0NMLjE3NDMwMTI0MzMuQ2owS0NRandxSW1fQmhEbkFSSXNBS0JZY211dXhkT0M4ZWwz
 a0tFMzUzSEpOTm5sOEJ6TThuUFRTRjRISEtYV0ZIRmExZThuTVBoQVN5d2FBbm5IRUFMd193Y
 0I.*_gcl_au*NjEyMjMwMTQ2LjE3NDM2OTEzNzc.">Since Russia's cyberattacks on 
 space-based services</a> provided by commercial US space companies during
  its war on Ukraine\, the cybersecurity of space systems has become high 
 on the agenda\, spurring discussions at the White House and in Congress\,
  and a <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/cloud-security/us-space-force
 -wants-700m-cybersecurity">$700 million budget request by the Space Force
 </a> for this purpose alone. At the same time\, <a href="https://www.inc.
 com/heather-wilde/harness-power-of-space-cybersecurity-for-growth-opportu
 nity.html">a fast-growing market has emerged</a>\, with demand for profes
 sionals and firms.</p><p>  Participants in the Space Cybersecurity Digita
 l Badge program will gain in-depth understanding of the various cyber thr
 eats to space systems as well as techniques\, tools\, and best practices 
 to address those threats. At the end of the program\, participants will h
 ave the capability to develop and implement effective strategies for mana
 ging cyber risks to space systems.</p><p>  After successful completion of
  an assurance of learning (assessment) at the conclusion of the program\,
  participants will earn the Kelley School of Business <strong>Space Cyber
 security Digital Badge</strong>. Participants may also earn 3 credit hour
 s toward the 12 credit hour Kelley School of Business Cybersecurity Manag
 ement Graduate Certificate. The <a href="https://kelley.iu.edu/programs/e
 xecutive-education-degrees-certificates/online-certificates/cybersecurity
 -management/index.html">Cybersecurity Management Graduate Certificate</a>
  may\, in turn\, be applied to the IU <a href="https://cyberrisk.iu.edu/?
 _gl=1*1833cq*_gcl_au*MTU3NDIzMTYyNy4xNzQ3MjMzNjYx*_ga*MTc4NDY5NDU2My4xNzM
 zNjM2NDc4*_ga_61CH0D2DQW*czE3NDcyMzA4OTkkbzIwJGcxJHQxNzQ3MjM2Mjc2JGo2MCRs
 MCRoMCRkMFdsRmYxSkwzaUs1bnoyYmNvdmVyY09qMlFscDFNV1R1QQ..">MS in Cybersecu
 rity Risk Management</a>.</p><p>  CISA designation: Your participation in
  this program and completion of all course requirements earns you 12.0 CP
 E credits that can go towards the annual credits you need to maintain you
 r CISA designation.</p><p>  * Space ISAC members receive exclusive discou
 nts of up to 50% based on membership tier. To learn about and obtain the 
 discount\, please reach out to Jade Maloney at <a href="mailto:jade@space
 isac.org">jade@spaceisac.org</a>.</p><p>  * GI/VA: We proudly welcome act
 ive-duty service members and veterans to the space cybersecurity program.
  Recognizing that GI Bill and VA education benefits do not apply to this 
 program\, IU is pleased to offer a Service Members &amp\; Veterans Schola
 rship amounting to 30% of the tuition. To receive the scholarship\, pleas
 e enter the code GI/VA30 during registration. Proof of military or vetera
 n status should be provided by the start date of the program.</p>
