SUMMARY:Kelley Teaching Seminar-Specifications Grading
DESCRIPTION:Facilitator: Eric Metzler  Faculty Panel:Joe Packowski\, Lect
 urer\, Honors Program Committee  Lynn Keller\, Lecturer\, Bus. Law &amp\;
  Ethics\, Co-chair Academic Fairness Committee  Rachel Landis\, Lecturer\
 , Teaching &amp\; Service Excellence Committee  Friday\, April 17th\, 202
 69:00 ŌĆō 10:00 a.m.HH 1043  Instructional Consulting has hosted a few se
 ssions in the past on the innovative grading system known as Specificatio
 ns Grading\, and now we would like to introduce the site we created to sh
 are further information about this exciting grading system as well as som
 e of the implementation strategies the panelists are currently using. Spe
 cifications Grading replaces points and partial credit with clear\, pass/
 fail "specifications\," which are tied to learning outcomes\, giving stud
 ents transparent choices and responsibility for their own success.  In th
 is Kelley Teaching Seminar\, we will share links to the new site\, includ
 ing videos and descriptions of how best to use this grading system. Panel
 ists will share examples from their teaching and answer any questions tha
 t arise about implementing Specifications Grading in your classroom.
