 , Lecturer\, Bus. Law &amp\; Ethics\, Co-chair Academic Fairness Committe
 e  </li><li><strong>Rachel Landis</strong>\, Lecturer\, Teaching &amp\; S
 ervice Excellence Committee  </li></ul><p><strong>Friday\, April 17th\, 2
 026</strong></p><p><strong>9:00 ŌĆō 10:00 a.m.</strong></p><p><strong>HH 
 1043</strong></p><p>  Instructional Consulting has hosted a few sessions 
 in the past on the innovative grading system known as <em>Specifications 
 Grading\,</em> and now we would like to introduce the site we created to 
 share further information about this exciting grading system as well as s
 ome of the implementation strategies the panelists are currently using. <
 em>Specifications Grading</em> replaces points and partial credit with cl
 ear\, pass/fail "specifications\," which are tied to learning outcomes\, 
 giving students transparent choices and responsibility for their own succ
 ess.</p><p>  In this Kelley Teaching Seminar\, we will share links to the
  new site\, including videos and descriptions of how best to use this gra
 ding system. Panelists will share examples from their teaching and answer
  any questions that arise about implementing <em>Specifications Grading</
 em> in your classroom.<br /><br /></p>
