SUMMARY:Strategic Thinking in U.S.-Africa Policy and Intelligence (w/ LUN
 CH)
DESCRIPTION:Event Description:  How do policymakers and intelligence offi
 cers navigate complex decisions in Africa and beyond?  Join Judd Devermon
 t (https://www.csis.org/people/judd-devermont)\, former National Intellig
 ence Officer for Africa and former Senior Director for African Affairs at
  the White House\, for a live\, scenario-driven session on strategy\, ris
 k\, and global policymaking.  Devermont spent over a decade in the intell
 igence community\, advised two administrations\, authored the U.S. Strate
 gy toward Sub-Saharan Africa\, and directed major initiatives shaping bil
 lions in infrastructure\, digital connectivity\, and energy investments.T
 his is not a lecture. You will work through a real-world scenario: Africa
 n states balancing relationships with the U.S. and China while managing d
 omestic political and development pressures.  You'll assess risk\, identi
 fy second- and third-order effects\, evaluate trade-offs\, and recommend 
 a course of action.What you'll gain:      Insight into how intelligence a
 nd policy intersect          Frameworks to anticipate unintended conseque
 nces          How analysis translates into real-world decisions          
 A window into careers in intelligence\, government\, and think tanks    L
 unch will be provided!&#160\;Come ready to debate\, analyze\, and defend 
 your conclusions in an interactive\, off-the-record setting.
